  "text": "Extraction of AAP. AAP was extracted by hot water and ultrasonic-assisted extraction. The concentrated supernatants were subsequently precipitated with 3 volumes of absolute ethanol (95%) and maintained at 4˚C overnight. The resulting precipitate was separated by centrifugation, dissolved in deionized water and subsequently dialyzed. The non-dialyzed portion was, in addition, lyophilized to result in a crude polysaccharide extract. The AAP was decolorized by hydrogen peroxide [CITATION_1] .",
